  "texts": [
    "These findings validate DRaFT-Q as a principled and general framework for scalable parameter-efficient adaptation.",
    "Scaling DRaFT-Q to Larger ModelsIn addition to Falcon-RW-1B experiments, we evaluated DRaFT-Q on larger models, including LLaMA-2-7B and LLaMA-2-13B, under tight memory budgets.",
    "These models were trained using 4-bit quantization for a single epoch on dialogue-style datasets such as OpenAssistant, OpenHermes, and UltraChat.Despite the scale difference, DRaFT-Q maintained stable convergence in under 1000 steps on the 7B model, achieving final training loss below 0.1 on both OpenAssistant and OpenHermes.",
    "On the 13B model, trained for only 800 steps on UltraChat due to resource constraints, the final loss was 1.289 and evaluation loss was 1.317.",
    "This underfitting stems from early stopping and limited adapter training time.Nonetheless, these experiments demonstrate that DRaFT-Q remains effective even at the 13B scale and can be optimized further with longer schedules or rank warm-up strategies."
  ],
